<section id="Changing_Views_for_Instances_and_Images" remap="TID_21619">
	<title>Changing Views for Instances and Images</title>
	<para>
		While you can set the default view for different pages in menu:Configuration[My Settings > Default Views], the current view can also be controlled from the Instances pages.
	</para>
	<procedure>
		<title>To Change the View of the Instance Pages</title>
		<step>
			<para>
				Navigate to menu:Clouds[Instances].
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click the accordion for the items to view.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click the appropriate button for the desired view.
			</para>
			<itemizedlist>
				<listitem>
					<para>
						Click 
						<inlinemediaobject>
							<imageobject>
								<imagedata fileref="images/2020.png" />
							</imageobject>
						</inlinemediaobject> for Grid View.
					</para>
				</listitem>
				<listitem>
					<para>
						Click 
						<inlinemediaobject>
							<imageobject>
								<imagedata fileref="images/2021.png" />
							</imageobject>
						</inlinemediaobject> for Tile View.
					</para>
				</listitem>
				<listitem>
					<para>
						Click 
						<inlinemediaobject>
							<imageobject>
								<imagedata fileref="images/2022.png" />
							</imageobject>
						</inlinemediaobject> for List View.
					</para>
				</listitem>
			</itemizedlist>
		</step>
	</procedure>
</section>
